For calculating the coefficients F1 and F8 one can takes an on-shell Q _Q pair with small relative momentum instead of the hadron in Eq. (2.4), and calculates oe(Q _Q) with perturbation theory. Then one also calculates the matrix elements in NRQCD with the same Q _Q pair. Substituting the results into Eq.(2.4) one can identify the coefficients. This is called matching. There will be I.R. divergences in oe(Q _Q) and also these I.R. divergences will appear in the matrix elements so that the coefficients are free from them.

According to Eq.(2.4) we can write the form for the gluon fragmentation function as:

