DO/J =G(z; _) = ^D1(z; J ) ! 0jOO/J1 (3PJ )j0 ? 1M 5 + ^D8(z) ! 0jOO/J8 (3S1)j0 ? 1M 3 (5:10) with ^D1(z; J ) and ^D8(z) given in Eq.(4.5), Eq.(4.6) and Eq.(5.9). Each component is now known to order ff2s. The nonperturbative effect is included in the two matrix elements. It is interesting to check whether the fragmentation functions calculated here satisfy their evolution equation. For gluon fragmentation the evolution equation reads

